            <thetext>Using the &quot;qx.ui.root.Inline&quot; class to use an element of the page for the root of a qooxdoo application fails when the options &quot;dynX&quot; and &quot;dynY&quot; are used.
These options change the behaviour of the inline to use the given dimension of the page element rather than let the application widgets determine the dimension.

With a given setup the inline DOM element grows indefinitely in both directions in IE.</thetext>
